        <num>CC 3257</num>
        <heading>3257.  Lessor's privilege primed by funeral charges</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3257.  Lessor's privilege primed by funeral charges.
The case is the same with respect to the funeral expenses of the debtor and his family; when there is no other source from which they can be paid, they have a preference over the debt for rent or hire, on the price of the movables contained in the house or on the farm.</p>
        </content>
